âœ… 1. What is Python?

Python is a high-level, easy-to-learn, general-purpose programming language.

âœ… 2. Why is Python called interpreted language?

Because Python code is executed line by line by the Python interpreter, not compiled into machine code directly.

âœ… 3. What are variables?

Variables are names used to store values in memory.

âœ… 4. What is indentation in Python?

Indentation means spaces at the beginning of a line; it defines code blocks (loops, functions, etc.).

âœ… 5. What are data types in Python?

Basic data types: int, float, str, bool, list, tuple, dict, set.

âœ… 6. What is list?

A list is a mutable, ordered collection of items.
Example: [1, 2, 3]

âœ… 7. What is tuple?

A tuple is an immutable, ordered collection of items.
Example: (1, 2, 3)

âœ… 8. Difference between list and tuple?

List â†’ mutable (can change)

Tuple â†’ immutable (cannot change)

âœ… 9. What is dictionary?

A dictionary is a keyâ€“value data structure.
Example: {"name": "Mahima", "age": 21}

âœ… 10. What is set?

A set is an unordered collection of unique items.
Example: {1, 2, 3}

âœ… 11. What is function in Python?

A function is a block of code that performs a specific task and is reused when called.

âœ… 12. What is lambda function?

A lambda is a small anonymous function defined using one line.
Example: lambda x: x * 2

âœ… 13. What is module?

A module is a Python file containing functions, classes, or variables.

âœ… 14. What is package?

A package is a collection of modules stored in a folder with an __init__.py file.

âœ… 15. What is OOP in Python?

OOP (Object-Oriented Programming) is a programming approach based on objects and classes.

âœ… 16. What is class?

A class is a blueprint used to create objects.

âœ… 17. What is object?

An object is an instance of a class that has data and behavior.

âœ… 18. What is constructor (__init__)?

__init__ is a special method that automatically runs when an object is created to initialize variables.

âœ… 19. What is inheritance?

Inheritance allows one class to acquire properties and methods of another class.

âœ… 20. What is exception handling?

Exception handling manages runtime errors using try, except, finally so the program doesn't crash.
